<Font|headerFont>HANGAR<Font|helpFont><p><p>

You begin a game in your team's Garrison hangar. The hangar
is the same in all landable stations. When you die in combat, and
eject pods are disabled, you will find yourself back at your Garrison
hangar unless there is another station closer to your point of death.<p><p>

Your <Main|hlpd1|Garrison>, as all other stations that you can build, has armor
protecting it, shown in the upper-left corner of your hangar. In
the upper center of your hangar is the name of the station and sector
you are currently in. If the station you are in is destroyed, then you'll be ejected
in the last ship type that you flew before landing at that station. If you
happened to
have just entered the game and the station you're in is destroyed,
you'll be
ejected in the first default ship in that station's Loadout screen.<p><p>

The message stream in the upper center of your
hangar is the same message stream you'll see while flying any ship.<p><p>

All the various in-game displays that you can access while flying your
ship can also be accessed from within your hangar, by either clicking
their location in the hangar or pressing the
corresponding key. In addition, the hangar is where you access your Loadout screen and
Teleport display.<p><p>

